Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When William Fernley was born in 1460, in Creeting St Peter, Suffolk, England, his father, John Farnley, was 50 and his mother, Lady Lavenia Whitaker, was 30. He had at least 1 son with Lady Margaret verch Thomas. He died in 1556, in Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 96."},"et":{"1460–1556":"1460–1556","1444–1499":"1444–1499","1490–1556":"1490–1556","1410–1459":"1410–1459","1430–1461":"1430–1461","1459":"1459","17 March 1499":"17. märts 1499","1556":"1556","1499":"1499","1444":"1444","1410":"1410","1430":"1430","1461":"1461","1460":"1460","1490":"1490","1549":"1549","Leeds, West Yorkshire, England":"Leeds, West Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Abergavenny, Monmouthshire, Wales":"Abergavenny, Monmouthshire, Wales","West Creting, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Creeting St Peter, Suffolk, England":"Creeting St Peter, Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"1460–1556":"1460–1556","1444–1499":"1444–1499","1490–1556":"1490–1556","1410–1459":"1410–1459","1430–1461":"1430–1461","1459":"1459","17 March 1499":"17. maaliskuuta 1499","1556":"1556","1499":"1499","1444":"1444","1410":"1410","1430":"1430","1461":"1461","1460":"1460","1490":"1490","1549":"1549","Leeds, West Yorkshire, England":"Leeds, West Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Abergavenny, Monmouthshire, Wales":"Abergavenny, Monmouthshire, Wales","West Creting, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Creeting St Peter, Suffolk, England":"Cree